      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 4,\n  \"summary\": \"The fix correctly unwraps the dict-shaped `gateway.auth` at the assembly boundary before `_clean_secret`, preserving its `str | None` contract. The downstream `_render_openclaw_json` re-wraps the bare token into `{mode, token}` at line 1750, so the round-trip is consistent. Test coverage verifies byte-identical output for both shapes. Three edge-case warnings remain: silent auth drop on missing dict key, mode overwrite for non-token dicts, and no guard against other unexpected types (list/int) that would hit the same `_clean_secret` crash class.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:585-587\",\n      \"issue\": \"Dict with missing `token` key (`{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\"}`) yields `auth_raw.get(\\\"token\\\", \\\"\\\")` → `\\\"\\\"` → `_clean_secret(\\\"\\\")` → `\\\"\\\"` → `GatewayInputs(auth=\\\"\\\")` → falsy → downstream drops the entire auth block (line 1749-1754). The operator declared `mode: token` (auth IS required) but gets no auth silently. A log warning or `AgentConfigError` would be safer than silent drop.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Consider: `if isinstance(auth_raw, dict) and \\\"token\\\" not in auth_raw: raise AgentConfigError(...)`, or at minimum log a warning. Alternatively use `auth_raw.get(\\\"token\\\")` (default `None`) so `_clean_secret(None) → \\\"\\\"` is more semantically explicit about 'absent'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:585-587\",\n      \"issue\": \"The unwrap extracts `.get(\\\"token\\\", \\\"\\\")` regardless of `auth_raw.get(\\\"mode\\\")`. If a future mode like `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"basic\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"\u003chex\u003e\\\"}` appeared, the token would be extracted and re-wrapped as `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": ...}` at line 1750 — silently changing the auth mode. Currently only `mode: token` is written by install.py, so this is theoretical.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a guard: `if isinstance(auth_raw, dict): if auth_raw.get(\\\"mode\\\") != \\\"token\\\": raise AgentConfigError(\\\"unsupported gateway.auth mode: ...\\\")`. This makes the normalization explicit about what shapes it accepts.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:585-587\",\n      \"issue\": \"No type guard for truly unexpected types (list, int, bool). `gateway_blob.get(\\\"auth\\\")` returning e.g. `12345` would bypass the `isinstance(auth_raw, dict)` check and hit `_clean_secret(12345)` → `value.replace(...)` → `AttributeError: 'int' object has no attribute 'replace'` — the same crash class as the original bug. In practice only dict and str shapes appear, but the single-condition check leaves the door open.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"After the dict unwrap, add: `if auth_raw is not None and not isinstance(auth_raw, str): raise AgentConfigError(\\\"gateway.auth has unexpected type: ...\\\")`. This closes the type contract completely.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/core/test_render.py:1303-1359\",\n      \"issue\": \"Test covers dict-with-token and bare-string shapes but not edge cases: dict missing `token` key, dict with `None` as token value, dict with non-`\\\"token\\\"` mode.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add parametrized sub-cases: `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\"}` (missing key), `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": None}`, `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"basic\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"x\\\"}`. For the first two, assert auth is empty/dropped. For the third, assert it raises `AgentConfigError` once the mode guard is added.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add an explicit type guard after the dict unwrap to reject non-str/non-dict/non-None values — closes the same crash class for list/int/bool.\",\n    \"Validate `mode == \\\"token\\\"` when auth is dict-