      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 2,\n  \"summary\": \"The new test proves the happy-path fix (bare string vs canonical dict both yield the same token) but leaves two blocking gaps: (1) non-dict non-string `auth` values (list, non-zero int) still reach `_clean_secret` and crash with AttributeError — the fix is incomplete; (2) `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\"}` with no `token` key silently assembles an empty bearer, violating the #437 gateway-token invariant with no test catching it. The test also violates the project's parametrize convention and the byte-identical assertion is weaker than it appears.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:585-587\",\n      \"issue\": \"The fix branches only on `isinstance(auth_raw, dict)`. If `auth_raw` is a non-empty list (e.g. `[\\\"tok\\\"]`) or a non-zero int, the branch is skipped and `_clean_secret(auth_raw)` calls `.replace()` on a non-string — the identical AttributeError the fix was meant to eliminate. The test never exercises these shapes, so the live bug path goes undetected.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Widen the guard: `if not isinstance(auth_raw, (str, type(None)))` (or an explicit `elif isinstance(auth_raw, dict)` else-raise) so every non-string, non-None, non-dict value is rejected at the assembler boundary. Add parametrized test cases for `auth=[\\\"tok\\\"]` and `auth=42` asserting either clean extraction or a clear AgentConfigError, never AttributeError.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:587 / tests/core/test_render.py:1303\",\n      \"issue\": \"`auth_raw.get(\\\"token\\\", \\\"\\\")` returns `\\\"\\\"` when the `token` key is absent (`{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\"}`). `_clean_secret(\\\"\\\")` returns `\\\"\\\"`. The agent sync completes without error but the daemon receives an empty bearer — every subsequent `clawctl agent chat` request gets 401. This violates AGENTS.md #437 (no silent-skip on gateway bearer). No test exercises this path.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"After extracting from the dict, treat an empty/missing token as a hard error: `if not auth_raw: raise AgentConfigError(\\\"gateway.auth dict missing 'token' field\\\")`. Add a test with `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\"}` asserting AgentConfigError is raised.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/core/test_render.py:1303\",\n      \"issue\": \"Test is not parametrized despite the project convention (compare `test_gateway_host_defaults_to_wildcard_when_blank` at line 1106 which uses `@pytest.mark.parametrize` for the same class of boundary inputs). Two sequential `_stores_with_auth` + `build_render_inputs` calls in a single test function obscure intent and make it easy to miss adding cases like `token=None`, `token=\\\"\\\"`, wrong mode, non-dict non-string.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Refactor into `@pytest.mark.parametrize(\\\"auth_value,expected_token\\\", [...])` covering: bare string, canonical dict, dict-missing-token-key (error), dict-token-None (error or empty), dict-token-empty-string (error or empty), wrong-mode dict, list, int.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/core/test_render.py:1354\",\n      \"issue\": \"`assert out_str.files == out_dict.files` only proves the two paths produce identical output — it does not independently verify either output is correct. If the normalization were broken and both paths returned `\\\"\\\"` for auth, this assertion would still pass. The mitigating `assert f'\\\"token\\\": \\\"{token}\\\"' in json_body` on line 1358 saves the happy path, but the assertion order implies byte-equivalence is the proof, which it is not.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Assert `inputs_dict.gateway.auth == token` before calling `render_openclaw` (token content, not just render-output equality). Then assert `f'\\\"token\\\": \\\"{token}\\\"' in out_dict.files[\\\".openclaw/openclaw.json\\\"]` independently for the dict path, not only via `out_str`. The byte-identical check can remain as a supplementary invariant.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/core/test_render.py:1281 / tests/core/test_render.py:1303\",\n      \"issue\": \"`test_clean_secret_applied_to_gateway_auth_and_api_server_key` (line 1281) covers NUL/CR/LF in `gateway.auth` for hermes only. Post-fix the openclaw path now unwraps the dict before calling `_clean_secret`, creating a new code path where a NUL-contaminated token value inside the dict (e.g. `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"abc\\\\x00def\\\"}`) is not tested. The existing test should gain an openclaw sibling or the new test should extend its parametrize to include control-character cases in the dict-token value.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"abc\\\\x00def\\\"}` as a parametrize case in the new test, asserting `inputs.gateway.auth == \\\"abcdef\\\"` after normalization.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/core/test_render.py:1303\",\n      \"issue\": \"`{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": None}` is not tested. `.get(\\\"token\\\", \\\"\\\")` returns `None` (key is present, default doesn't fire). `_clean_secret(None)` returns `\\\"\\\"` silently. This is the same silent empty-bearer failure as the missing-key case, but through a different code path.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Covered by the parametrize refactor recommended in W2 above. Assert either AgentConfigError or document None-token as intentional-empty in a test that explicitly names the behavior.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/core/test_render.py:1303\",\n      \"issue\": \"The docstring claims the pre-fix bug was an AttributeError from `_clean_secret` receiving a dict, but there is no `pytest.raises` or `xfail` assertion that would catch a regression if the fix were reverted. A reader must trust the narrative in the docstring.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a focused one-liner that directly calls `_clean_secret({\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"x\\\"})` and asserts it raises AttributeError — pin the pre-fix failure mode as an explicit invariant so reverting the dict-unwrap is immediately caught.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/core/test_render.py:1303\",\n      \"issue\": \"`{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"basic\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"abc\\\"}` is not tested. The fix extracts `token` regardless of the `mode` field value. It is ambiguous whether this is intentional (mode is advisory and ignored) or a latent bug (should raise on unrecognized mode). No test documents the intended behavior.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a parametrize case for wrong-mode dict. If the intent is mode-agnostic extraction, assert `gateway.auth == \\\"abc\\\"` and add a comment. If mode must equal `\\\"token\\\"`, add a guard and test for AgentConfigError on wrong-mode input.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Widen the isinstance guard in render.py:585-587 to reject non-dict, non-string, non-None auth values with AgentConfigError rather than letting them fall through to _clean_secret.\",\n    \"Treat an empty/missing `token` key inside the dict as a hard AgentConfigError, not a silent empty string — the #437 invariant makes an empty bearer a correctness failure.\",\n    \"Refactor test_gateway_auth_accepts_dict_and_string_shapes_openclaw into a @pytest.mark.parametrize table covering all boundary shapes (missing key, None token, empty-string token, NUL-in-token, wrong mode, list, int) per the project convention established by test_gateway_host_defaults_to_wildcard_when_blank.\",\n    \"Assert token content independently for the dict render path (out_dict.files) rather than relying solely on byte-identity with out_str.files.\",\n    \"Extend test_clean_secret_applied_to_gateway_auth_and_api_server_key or the new test to cover NUL/CR/LF inside the dict-token value for openclaw, closing the NUL-contamination gap opened by the new dict-unwrap code path.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 2,\n    \"domain\": \"test-coverage / gateway-token-normalization\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
